benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/catalog/xml - Upload the full catalog as XML

covered: Valid Payload scenarios are covered by TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC13, TC21, TC22.
Invalid Payload scenarios covered: TC08 (malformed XML), TC09 (empty body), TC10 (invalid content type), TC18 (partial/corrupted XML), TC23 (whitespace-only), TC17 (XML with unsafe content).
Validation across payload variations: TC30 (boundary values), TC24 (special chars/unicode), TC29 (encodings), TC27 (headers with whitespace), TC28 (XML comments/CDATA).
Server error handling covered: TC16 (backend down, 503).
Authorization scenarios covered: TC06 (missing CreatedBy header) and TC14 (invalid authentication).
gaps: Caching behavior headers tested (ETag, Cache-Control) missing.
Additional 5xx server errors beyond 503 (e.g., 500 Internal Server Error) not tested.
Token expiry / revocation scenarios beyond missing/invalid.
recommendations: Add rate limiting tests to verify behavior under high request rates.
Add caching header tests (ETag, Cache-Control) for POST responses.
Include 500 Internal Server Error scenarios to ensure proper 500 handling.
Expand authorization testing to include token expiry/revocation scenarios, not just missing/invalid tokens.
Test boundary header values (length/format) and other unusual but valid header combinations.
